This is working currently in the testing branch:

{code}
# euca-modify-property -p loadbalancing.loadbalancer_emi=emi-0A8636ED
PROPERTY	loadbalancing.loadbalancer_emi	emi-0A8636ED was NULL
{code}

Can you provide more details on the build of 3.3.0 that you are running?

That should be fine. Next we can take a look at the configuration database. Please run the following command as root while your cloud is running:

{code}
# psql -h /var/lib/eucalyptus/db/data/ -p 8777 eucalyptus_config -c "select * from config_static_property where config_static_prop_name = 'loadbalancing.loadbalancer_emi';"
{code}

While collecting information, we might as well see what the services look like so please also post the output from:

{code}
# euca-describe-services
{code}
